"Feature name: Memory
Used to check flash, file system and partition information.
It supports EMMC and NAND flash.
There are 3 tabs for detailed information:
flash common information, file system information and partition information.
"

"Feature name: CPU Stress Test
Used to do CPU stress test. It support for single core and dual core.
There are 3 items for test: AP MCU, SW Video Codec, Clock Switch.
AP MCU: contains NEON test and MaxPower test.
SW Video Codec: run software video codec test.
Clock Switch: switch CA9 clock between CLKSQ and ARMPLL.
"

"Feature name: CPU Stress Test
Used to do CPU stress test. It support for single core, dual core and quad core.
There are 3 items for test: AP MCU, SW Video Codec, Clock Switch.
AP MCU: contains VFP test, MaxPower test, Dhrystone test, L2 MEMCPY test, FDCT test and IMDCT test.
SW Video Codec: run software video codec test.
Clock Switch: switch clock between CLKSQ and ARMPLL.
"

"Feature name: Camera.
AF EM item used to set capture auto focus mode.
Raw Capture Mode item used to select raw capture mode.
Raw Type item used to select store what kind of raw file.
Flicker item used to set camera\'s Anti-fiicker value.
ISO item used to set camera\'s iso value.
Start Preview item to open the camera and start camera preview, in the preview page, press Capture button will take picture(s) with the previous settings. The picture(s) will be store in the path: SDCard//DCIM//EMCamera."

"Feature name: WiFi
Used to do WiFi test and check WiFi status by RD.
There are 4 test items: Tx, Rx, MCR, NVRAM and some check boxes as a switch.
Tx: Test WiFi send packages at different frequencies, rates, power and so on. It needs special instruments to analyze the results.
Rx: Test WiFi receive packages at different frequencies and bandwidth. It will show the results of received packages.
MCR: Read and write WiFi control register. Warning: The operation of non-professionals is forbidden.
NVRAM: Read and write WiFi NVRAM, could accessed in word or byte string.
Switch: Some switches used by RD.
"
